Bauchi Governor Bala Mohammed has offered N2 million as compensation for information that will lead to safe return  of his abducted brother. Nation reports that unknown gunmen whisked away the governor’s elder brother, Adamu Mohammed  about 7pm  at Kobi  street in Bauchi metropolis last Wednesday. The reward on information leading to his safe return was disclosed in a press statement in Bauchi, the state capital on Sunday  by the Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on Media, Mukhtar Gidado. The statement reads: ‘ The family wishes to offer the sum of two million Naira (N 2 million) to whoever is willing to provide information leading to his safe return.”